  "An astronomer notices that Mars appears to move backward among the stars for several weeks. Which model BEST explains this simply?": "",
  "The heliocentric model — Earth overtakes Mars in its orbit, creating apparent backward motion": "",
  "Mars is slowing down due to friction in space": "",
  "Mars is being pulled backward by Jupiter's gravity": "",
  "The geocentric model — Mars actually reverses its orbit periodically": "",
  "Retrograde motion is elegantly explained by the heliocentric model: Earth, in a faster inner orbit, overtakes Mars. The apparent backward motion is like a slower car appearing to drift backward as you pass it on a highway.": "",
  "A student reads that Ptolemy's model required over 80 circles while Copernicus's needed far fewer. What scientific principle does this illustrate?": "",
