  "Simplicity (Occam's Razor) — simpler explanations are generally preferred": "",
  "Relativity — all motion is relative to the observer": "",
  "Occam's Razor suggests that the simplest explanation fitting the data is usually the best. Copernicus's heliocentric model explained the same observations with far fewer assumptions.": "",
  "Galileo observed that Venus shows a full range of phases (like the Moon). Why did this challenge the geocentric model?": "",
